com.sun.tools.visualvm.core.model
Interface ModelProvider<M extends Model,B extends DataSource>

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractModelProvider, ApplicationTypeFactory, DataSourceDescriptorFactory, EclipseApplicationTypeFactory, HostOverviewFactory, IntellijApplicationTypeFactory, JavaPluginApplicationTypeFactory, JavaWebStartApplicationTypeFactory, JDeveloperApplicationTypeFactory, JvmFactory, MainClassApplicationTypeFactory, MavenApplicationTypeFactory, NetBeansApplicationTypeFactory
public interface ModelProvider<M extends Model,B extends DataSource>

This interface should be implemented if you want to extend ModelFactory with your own provider. Implementors of this ModelProvider inteface should be registered with appropriate ModelFactory using ModelFactory.registerProvider(ModelProvider)

Author:
Tomas Hurka

Method Detail

createModelFor

M createModelFor(B dataSource)
This is factory method for creating new instance of Model for DataSource. Implementation of this method should return null if this model provider cannot construct model for passed dataSource.

Parameters:
dataSource - DataSource for which Model should be created
Returns:
model subclass for dataSource

priority

int priority()
Priority is used by ModelFactory to sort registered ModelProvider. Model provider with the highest priority will be invoked first and so no, until non-null value is returned from createModelFor(DataSource )

Returns:
priority of this ModelProvider
